      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SMART MINX (2) comes off an average performance last start when sixth at this track over 388m behind Morning Daylight (22.80) in a Grade 5. Was a winner the start prior. Comes through a solid form race last start. Tough to beat if on-song. CHIEF ENFORCER (1) produced a modest effort most recently when fifth at The Gardens over 400m behind Zipping Deloris (23.10) in a Grade 5. Was in the money the start prior. Reliable out of the boxes and should take advantage of the inside draw. Has ability and is one of the better chances. NOVA LASS (8) had been racing well prior to her last start fifth at this track following a Grade 5 win three back with a third placing. Safe beginner but wide box to overcome and will need some luck. Expected to bounce back to best. REAL EXPRESS (3) form at this course and distance reads well.",
